The paper deals with a problem in supervised learning and proposes a novel loss function for multiset prediction. The problem is related to sequential decision making and involves predicting a multiset consisting of multiple items without any known order among them. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
